comments.commentBody:
@Jon W.<br/>
     Ah, you're just being cranky.<br/>
     New York invented highways.  Remember the TriBorough Authority.  As for bridge maintenance take a ride across the Brooklyn Bridge and see the tremendous restoration project.  As for retiree pensions, almost all that money stays in New York.  New York still has the greatest teaching hospitals in the world and the greatest medical care.  As for taxes, you get what you pay for - there are no free rides.  Finally, as for running out of money, look at all the foreign money pouring into the city.  If you think not, try and buy an apartment in Manhattan.
